# =============================================================================
# BACKEND .dockerignore
# =============================================================================
# Works exactly like .gitignore but for Docker's COPY/ADD commands.
# Files listed here are EXCLUDED from the build context sent to Docker.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
# 1. node_modules  → We install fresh inside the container (npm ci).
#                    Copying local node_modules would break things because
#                    native binaries are compiled for your OS, not the
#                    container's Linux environment.
# 2. .env files    → Never bake secrets into an image. Secrets are injected
#                    at runtime via environment variables.
# 3. Large dirs    → Smaller build context = faster `docker build`.
# =============================================================================

# Dependencies — reinstalled inside the container
node_modules

# Env files — secrets are injected at runtime, never baked into the image
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# Git history — not needed in the container
.git
.gitignore

# Editor and OS files
.DS_Store
.vscode
*.swp
